WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:22.080
My name is Quincy Howe.

00:22.080 --> 00:26.960
My job is to report and comment on the news for ABC, radio and television.

00:26.960 --> 00:33.180
My assignment here in Miami is to discuss the campaign issues with Estes Keapover and

00:33.180 --> 00:36.520
Adley Stevenson, who are our chief performers this evening.

00:36.520 --> 00:40.480
Now there's no need to introduce the two top contenders, the Democratic presidential

00:40.480 --> 00:41.480
nomination.

00:41.480 --> 00:47.960
And I can let them define as well as discuss the issues, but just a brief word on the

00:47.960 --> 00:50.480
background I think is in order.

00:50.480 --> 00:56.520
Mr. Sanitak Keapover got off to a strong start in his primary race by winning Minnesota,

00:56.520 --> 01:00.360
Governor Stevenson came back strong in our gun last week.

01:00.360 --> 01:05.000
A week from tomorrow, they go before the voters of Florida, the registered voters here

01:05.000 --> 01:10.400
in the primaries here, the week after that, another big primary in California.

01:10.400 --> 01:15.200
So those primaries on top of the our gun won are just about bringing this primary phase

01:15.200 --> 01:20.480
of the convention of the race for the presidential nomination and the Democratic party to the

01:20.480 --> 01:25.640
climates, which makes this evening the time in Miami the place for these friendly rivals

01:25.640 --> 01:28.840
to discuss the issues of the campaign.

01:28.840 --> 01:34.120
I'm very deeply honored to find myself here as moderator and I'm also intensely nervous

01:34.120 --> 01:37.760
because of the triple responsibility that lies upon me.

01:37.760 --> 01:43.240
First is Senator Keapover, second to Governor Stevenson, and third to those who look and

01:43.240 --> 01:44.240
listen in.

01:44.240 --> 01:49.760
I must see that the time is fairly divided, that I state the issues as impartially as it

01:49.760 --> 01:54.240
is humanly possible for me to do, and that there is a full and very discussion of the

01:54.240 --> 01:55.240
issues.

01:55.240 --> 01:58.760
And then there's an agreement on the format that's going to be a three minute opening statement

01:58.760 --> 02:01.760
from each of the two gentlemen here in a five minute closing.

02:01.760 --> 02:07.560
A toss of the coin decided that Senator Keapover would open, then Governor Stevenson, then

02:07.560 --> 02:13.040
at the close, Governor Stevenson first and Senator Keapover closes up the whole thing.

02:13.040 --> 02:18.160
In between there'll be freewheeling talk in which I act as a kind of a traffic cop with

02:18.160 --> 02:22.560
power to hand out parking tickets if anyone stays too long in one place or to enforce speed

02:22.560 --> 02:24.440
limits if they get going too fast.

02:24.440 --> 02:27.440
And I hope there won't be any occasion to do either.

02:27.440 --> 02:32.560
So first Senator Keapover, and if any of you want to know what he is going to talk about,

02:32.560 --> 02:36.880
the answer is about three minutes and I hope it won't be too much more.

02:36.880 --> 02:42.200
Thank you very much, Mr. Howard, Governor Stevenson, good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

02:42.200 --> 02:47.920
A presidential campaign must not degenerate into a mere personal conflict.

02:47.920 --> 02:52.280
For candidates are only as important as the ideas they represent.

02:52.920 --> 02:58.120
Now therefore welcome this opportunity for this discussion with Mr. Stevenson.

02:58.120 --> 03:04.200
Overshadowing all else is this morning's news of the first dropping from an American

03:04.200 --> 03:07.200
airplane of an H bomb.

03:07.200 --> 03:12.760
There can be no mistaking effect that we are now face to face with a double-edged possibility

03:12.760 --> 03:18.360
of total destruction and the possession of total destructive power.

03:18.360 --> 03:24.400
We are perhaps being dominated by the very instrumentalities which we ourselves have created.

03:24.400 --> 03:29.600
And unless we can forge some readjustment of our organization and management of political

03:29.600 --> 03:37.200
affairs, we shall never again live unafraid and undominated by these fearful prospects.

03:37.200 --> 03:42.040
Unless we can successfully grapple with this, we shall never again be free in the sense

03:42.040 --> 03:46.720
that we can make our own choices and live in confidence.

03:46.720 --> 03:50.520
Next we must have a moral, atomic energy policy.

03:50.520 --> 03:57.520
Second we must continue to experiment and test and develop new and extended uses of nuclear

03:57.520 --> 03:58.720
energy.

03:58.720 --> 04:04.920
We should however take the lead in proposing to the Soviet Union that we have an immediate

04:04.920 --> 04:10.240
cessation of further dropping of A in H bombs when they show that they are willing to act

04:10.240 --> 04:12.400
in good faith.

04:12.400 --> 04:17.680
Without the protection of such an agreement, we ourselves have little choice but to continue

04:17.680 --> 04:20.320
in the interest of our own security.

04:20.320 --> 04:24.920
Our favorite, the so-called Baruch Plan when it was first presented.

04:24.920 --> 04:29.680
Substantially that plan with emphasis on inspections should now be resubmitted.

04:29.680 --> 04:35.760
I think the very dropping of this new bomb may give new hope of success in achieving such

04:35.760 --> 04:37.440
agreements.

04:37.440 --> 04:42.680
Substantialists, Belman everywhere, must realize that we cannot leave this destructive force

04:42.680 --> 04:45.440
loose in the world uncurred.

04:45.440 --> 04:50.440
We need a crash program to ensure that the nation is producing scientists, both highly

04:50.440 --> 04:56.320
qualified and insufficient numbers, second to none in the world.

04:56.320 --> 05:02.600
The national interest demands a truly non-political and independent, atomic energy commission.

05:02.600 --> 05:07.920
We need a nationwide program to turn the benefits of atomic energy to peaceful uses in

05:07.920 --> 05:08.920
our economy.

05:08.920 --> 05:14.680
Our favorite government-sponsored program for the establishment of atomic federal projects

05:14.680 --> 05:17.400
in the key areas throughout the country.

05:17.400 --> 05:22.120
We must ensure that there is no private monotony in atomic energy.

05:22.120 --> 05:28.680
Finally, we must find means of transforming this machine of total destruction into an instrument

05:28.680 --> 05:30.600
for lasting peace.

05:30.600 --> 05:36.280
We must turn its very terrible into the last best argument for world peace.

05:36.280 --> 05:40.520
We cannot continue along a path, past hope and fear.

05:40.520 --> 05:43.240
Perfect timing, Senator Kepler.

05:43.240 --> 05:45.840
And now Governor Stevenson, the offering minutes.

05:45.840 --> 05:53.000
Mr. Howe, you said something about the root, what's the basis, what's the principle

05:53.000 --> 05:57.120
subject of the principle concern of our country in this campaign?

05:57.120 --> 06:00.560
I think perhaps the senators touched upon it as I see it.

06:00.560 --> 06:05.720
Certainly the solemnity of the time in which we live was best illustrated yesterday by

06:05.720 --> 06:09.480
the dropping of the H-bomb in the far Pacific.

06:09.480 --> 06:19.280
A bomb five times or more, more powerful than all of the explosive detonated by the United

06:19.280 --> 06:21.800
States in the last war.

06:21.800 --> 06:30.560
I thought when I read of this, not only that the future is either going to be a future

06:30.560 --> 06:37.080
of creativity and of great abundance, or it's going to be a future of total incineration,

06:37.080 --> 06:43.440
death and destruction, and that the United States may have to lead the way which direction

06:43.440 --> 06:45.320
we're going to take.

06:45.320 --> 06:51.280
I thought of the remark of the interesting phrase that President Sikarno of Indonesia used

06:51.280 --> 06:55.080
for the spoke to the Congress the other day in which he said that he had come to the United

06:55.080 --> 06:56.560
States.

06:56.560 --> 07:03.240
Not just to see the great United States, not just to learn something about this center of

07:03.240 --> 07:08.280
geography and of the balanced power in the world and the center of gravity, but because

07:08.280 --> 07:13.320
he wanted to come here because it was the center of an idea.

07:13.320 --> 07:18.520
It's this idea that I think is the at the heart of this campaign.

07:18.520 --> 07:19.680
What is America about?

07:19.680 --> 07:24.920
What does it mean in this midpoint of the 20th century when these great revolutions of

07:24.920 --> 07:30.000
technology that have developed this bomb which have made all men neighbors, when the great

07:30.000 --> 07:36.120
revolution of independence which has swept over Asia, the great revolution, the great

07:36.120 --> 07:42.600
ideological revolution which threatens us from the East communism have all converged.

07:42.600 --> 07:45.160
This I think is what we have to demonstrate and quickly.

07:45.160 --> 07:47.480
We are great, but we are few.

07:47.480 --> 07:52.520
We have 50% of the world's manufacturers, but only 6% of the world's population.

07:52.520 --> 07:58.440
We have to import 50% of our raw materials.

07:58.440 --> 08:01.240
The balance with our allies, we constitute what?

08:01.240 --> 08:05.640
But 15% of the world, the enemy constitutes 35%.

08:05.640 --> 08:08.640
Together we 50%.

08:08.640 --> 08:09.640
What's the rest?

08:09.640 --> 08:12.440
The rest is the great uncommitted peoples of the earth.

08:12.440 --> 08:16.440
These are the peoples that we're going to contest for as long ideas as many of us are

08:16.440 --> 08:17.440
living.

08:17.440 --> 08:20.160
We're here witnessing this program tonight.

08:20.160 --> 08:25.720
And it's until the United States assumes once more leadership in this world, leadership

08:25.720 --> 08:31.040
in the direction of peace on earth until we once more can assert the moral influence that

08:31.040 --> 08:32.920
we have enjoyed in the past.

08:32.920 --> 08:38.520
It's three years ago we were both great and we were also we commanded confidence and we

08:38.520 --> 08:39.600
were respected.

08:39.600 --> 08:41.800
We were strong and we were respected.

08:41.800 --> 08:45.720
We're not as strong today as we are that we're then nor are we as respected.

08:45.720 --> 08:48.080
We have to recover on both scores.

08:48.080 --> 08:53.160
Now I should very be very glad as the evening goes on here to talk a little about the H-bomb.

08:53.160 --> 08:56.440
I've made some proposals with respect to that myself.

08:56.440 --> 09:01.840
But I know that most of all, Mr. Howell that the what's at the center of this campaign

09:01.840 --> 09:06.840
in my judgment is the assumption once more of leadership in the world in the direction

09:06.840 --> 09:12.080
of the peace that has become the prayer of all mankind and most of all of our people in

09:12.080 --> 09:13.080
this country.

09:13.080 --> 09:14.080
Thank you, Governor Stevenson.

09:14.080 --> 09:18.720
And I think since we've gotten into this foreign policy and bomb subject, let's stay

09:18.720 --> 09:19.720
with it.

09:19.720 --> 09:25.800
Senator Kiefover made a remark in his talk suggesting that perhaps we should cut down on these

09:25.800 --> 09:26.800
H-bomb tests.

09:26.800 --> 09:29.120
How about getting a little more practical?

09:29.120 --> 09:32.920
What precise steps would you suggest taking from here on out, Senator?

09:32.920 --> 09:33.920
What should we do?

09:33.920 --> 09:34.920
These would be the rules.

09:34.920 --> 09:42.480
Well, Mr. Howell, the matter that I said forth was that while we've always wanted

09:42.480 --> 09:47.360
and we're anxious now to reach some agreement, we've referenced to the control of atomic

09:47.360 --> 09:53.880
energy and for its use for key-stamp purposes for the welfare of our people, the thing is

09:53.880 --> 10:00.040
that it's inconsistent to criticize the administration and to complain that we're not keeping up or

10:00.040 --> 10:04.880
that we're not ahead of the Soviet Union in the making of guided missiles and atomic

10:04.880 --> 10:06.200
energy.

10:06.200 --> 10:11.920
And at the same time not be willing until we can get some good faith agreement from them,

10:11.920 --> 10:19.880
not be willing to experiment and to explode or to use the bombs that we make because only

10:19.880 --> 10:26.040
by experimenting with them can we keep ahead so that I do not think we can propose acting

10:26.040 --> 10:32.720
unilaterally and stopping the dropping of atomic bombs as I understand my friend, Governor

10:32.720 --> 10:34.720
Stevenson has proposed.

10:34.720 --> 10:39.200
Do you want to go along on that line, Governor Stevenson, you've come out in opposition

10:39.200 --> 10:40.200
to the H-bomb test?

10:40.200 --> 10:43.560
Well, sir, I have said this.

10:43.560 --> 10:49.640
I have said that I've pointed out that the Soviet Union has recently told us in London

10:49.640 --> 10:55.520
that the open sky's proposal of inspection by aviation by air was fantastic, where the

10:55.520 --> 10:57.080
words that Mr. Kruchef used.

10:57.080 --> 11:02.040
It's apparent that we're making no progress nor have we in the past ten years towards

11:02.040 --> 11:05.640
the step-by-step disarmament program.

11:05.640 --> 11:11.320
Now with respect to the H-bomb, the H-bomb cannot be tested without all the world knowing

11:11.320 --> 11:12.800
it.

11:12.800 --> 11:13.800
This is my understanding.

11:13.800 --> 11:15.720
I believe this is the case.

11:15.720 --> 11:21.000
If that's so, it has the advantage of not requiring inspection to know whether or not

11:21.000 --> 11:26.080
the enemy is complying with an agreement or is not complying with an agreement.

11:26.080 --> 11:30.120
It has its own built-in security factor.

11:30.120 --> 11:35.520
The Soviet Union has, unhappily, and I think it's one of the great ironies of our time.

11:35.520 --> 11:40.280
It's now succeeded in masquerading as the friend of these uncommitted peoples is half of

11:40.280 --> 11:45.160
the world that I mentioned, which is where rests the balance of power in the world and

11:45.160 --> 11:47.120
where rests I think are destiny.

11:47.120 --> 11:51.880
I think it's imperative that the United States takes some leadership towards recapturing

11:51.880 --> 11:53.280
the confidence of these people.

11:53.280 --> 11:54.280
What else should we do?

11:54.280 --> 11:55.280
We could do it.

11:55.280 --> 12:00.320
Yeah, because of the built-in factor of security, due to the fact that you cannot test an H-bomb

12:00.320 --> 12:04.480
without it being known everywhere, is that we could unilaterally propose that we would

12:04.480 --> 12:11.040
discontinue testing the H-bomb on condition, of course, that if our enemies did not go along

12:11.040 --> 12:15.400
with this and do the same, we would know about it and we could resume the testing of the

12:15.400 --> 12:16.400
H-bomb.

12:16.400 --> 12:19.200
That this distinguishes this weapon from everything else.

12:19.200 --> 12:22.000
It has no relationship to the guided missile, whatever.

12:22.000 --> 12:28.400
Well, Mr. Howard, I think the difficulty is, though, that it's reputed that the Soviet

12:28.400 --> 12:31.960
have already dropped the H-bomb from an airplane.

12:31.960 --> 12:37.600
Of course, this test in specific, which Governor Stevenson proposed, his iron studage, should

12:37.600 --> 12:43.360
not take place, was for the development of a new use of the weapon.

12:43.360 --> 12:49.600
Now, we can't very well afford to fuss about not keeping up in these weapons and the

12:49.600 --> 12:55.320
in atomic energy if we are unable to experiment with them and to see what they will do.

12:56.040 --> 12:59.800
Now, I certainly agree that we ought to make it very clear to everyone in the world that

12:59.800 --> 13:05.000
we are perfectly willing to devote atomic energy and our research and share it with people

13:05.000 --> 13:06.840
when it can be shared everywhere.

13:06.840 --> 13:14.840
Of course, they, because the war of ideas is important and we are the must be, as we've

13:14.840 --> 13:19.400
always been, the real friends of people who want to develop their resources and get their

13:19.400 --> 13:20.400
liberty.

13:20.480 --> 13:26.080
But we cannot afford to allow any other power to have greater strength in atomic energy

13:26.080 --> 13:28.560
and guided missiles than we have.

13:28.560 --> 13:29.760
And I didn't like very much.

13:29.760 --> 13:35.280
Frankly, the statement by Mr. Kruchev when he was in England indicating that the Soviets

13:35.280 --> 13:37.600
were going right ahead with their missile program.

13:38.720 --> 13:43.920
I want to see some good faith before I stop keeping the defenses of the United States strong.

13:43.920 --> 13:47.600
Let's get on to some more of these features of the Russian new look.

13:47.600 --> 13:49.680
This military come back and that kind of thing.

13:49.680 --> 13:51.040
I think that you've made your position.

13:51.040 --> 13:55.840
We got through with a bomb something about what we ought to do with the atomic energy

13:55.840 --> 14:00.560
program and developing it for commercial purposes if we may.

14:00.560 --> 14:05.360
Yes, I'd like very much if I could point out to the senator that the I have never suggested

14:05.360 --> 14:07.680
post-pony development of the missile on the contrary.

14:07.680 --> 14:09.760
I've urged the development of the missile.

14:09.760 --> 14:12.480
This is a weapon that could be tested without anyone knowing it.

14:12.480 --> 14:16.400
It has none of the built-in security features of knowledge and information.

14:17.120 --> 14:20.960
Therefore, when the president said that the missile and the bomb to develop one

14:20.960 --> 14:23.120
with the other was useless, I didn't understand it.

14:23.120 --> 14:25.120
Frankly, no, do I think he understood me?

14:25.760 --> 14:26.960
The missile can be developed.

14:26.960 --> 14:28.240
It should be developed.

14:28.240 --> 14:33.680
Or weapons should be developed so that we can keep pace with our enemies.

14:33.680 --> 14:34.960
Indeed, we must keep ahead of them.

14:35.760 --> 14:40.080
The what I am talking about is the most lethal, the most terrible, the most devastating,

14:40.080 --> 14:43.760
the most ghastly weapon that has been developed on the face of the earth.

14:44.320 --> 14:48.000
We have the power of self-suicide, a destruction of the world.

14:48.000 --> 14:53.360
And I said that this one could be eliminated if they would agree with security,

14:53.360 --> 14:54.960
because we'll know it if they're not.

14:55.520 --> 14:56.160
And what's happening?

14:56.160 --> 14:57.360
If they're not the right amount of time.

