17:07.040 --> 17:11.600
A private industry probably rightfully says it cannot invest the money to assume this

17:11.600 --> 17:14.400
responsibility. They shouldn't have asked for it in the first place.

17:15.280 --> 17:17.040
So I think the times come when our

17:17.920 --> 17:26.400
atomic energy act of 1954 must be revised so that the government can experiment and build

17:26.400 --> 17:29.200
these reactors throughout many parts of the country.

17:30.000 --> 17:34.960
I know the state of Florida has been doing a lot of work trying to get one established here.

17:35.520 --> 17:40.640
Rather do not have power and coal and of course it's in places like that where they should be built.

17:41.440 --> 17:46.640
And we must get the atomic energy commission back to the business of commercial development

17:46.640 --> 17:50.800
and dealing with atoms and out of such matters as Dixon and Yeats.

17:50.800 --> 17:55.760
Well I'd like to get Mr. Steeves and Governor Steeves and others some of the diplomatic features

17:55.920 --> 18:01.520
of this new Soviet look both in connection with the downgrading of Stalin, the military cut back and

18:01.520 --> 18:06.880
so on. There's a great deal of controversy over that. It cuts across party, across national lines.

18:06.880 --> 18:11.440
Are we being too gullible? Tought the Russians, some people say we're too simple minded. Other

18:11.440 --> 18:17.840
people say we aren't tough that we're we should be more kindly and we are too negative and too rigid.

18:17.840 --> 18:21.280
I'd like to hear what you have to say about that. Governor, you've been around the world recently.

18:21.760 --> 18:27.680
How did you find people reacted? Let me say that I should like to say to Senator that I agree with

18:27.680 --> 18:32.240
much of what he has just said. I would point out too that nothing could be more ironic.

18:32.240 --> 18:36.640
Then in the present contest that we're in with the Russians which I will get to which is for the

18:37.600 --> 18:43.920
allegiance of these uncommitted peoples, these neutral peoples and that depends largely on who

18:44.480 --> 18:49.760
is going to how that rapidly they can fulfill the promise of their revolutions, they can improve

18:49.760 --> 18:55.040
their standard living and their well-being, they would be ironic indeed if the Soviet Union

18:55.840 --> 19:01.440
beat the United States to the development of reactors which could be used by for power development

19:01.440 --> 19:07.840
in these power hungry countries who are trying so desperately to to industrialize at long last.

19:08.480 --> 19:14.240
And there I think again what the Senator implied is correct that the public in the United

19:14.320 --> 19:19.760
States have invested somewhat $14 billion in the development of atomic and nuclear energy

19:20.320 --> 19:26.720
and that we should be frustrated and the further development for peaceful purposes to use

19:26.720 --> 19:32.960
abroad as well as here. Yes, and we should ever be outdone by the Soviet Union would be a

19:32.960 --> 19:38.560
sad thing indeed. Now you asked me about the cut in the military forces of the Soviet Union,

19:38.560 --> 19:44.880
they were ground forces. Yes, million two. It was a spectacular propaganda stroke and it's had

19:44.880 --> 19:53.200
undoubtedly widespread effect in Asia as evidence of the peaceful ideas of the peaceful desires of

