the Soviet Union. It's another reason why I think that we are going to have to come up with some

19:58.240 --> 20:03.200
ingenious ideas if we're going to compete for their allegiance especially in the direction of peace.

20:03.280 --> 20:08.640
I think that the cut was of no significance because of the change in the character of warfare.

20:08.640 --> 20:14.000
Immediately after the war we had a monopoly of atomic weapons. We also had the means of their

20:14.000 --> 20:20.080
delivery by aircraft superiority. All the Soviet Union could do was develop ground forces to

20:20.080 --> 20:25.680
in order to envelop the continent of Europe if need be to interdict our bases. And so on now that

20:25.680 --> 20:30.880
they likewise have the means of delivery and the weapon itself they can afford to change their

20:30.880 --> 20:37.520
tactics which are their military structure and that they have done. They have done it also because

20:37.520 --> 20:43.520
of its propaganda value also because it will strike a sentimental and sympathetic code in the west

20:43.520 --> 20:50.000
where we all want to cut forces to save money especially in Western Europe and also because of its

20:50.000 --> 20:56.000
enormous propaganda value in Asia. Now as a legislator, Senator Keifalba, how do you find your

20:56.000 --> 21:00.560
constituents respond on these issues that we're talking about now? Other votes in these things?

21:01.200 --> 21:06.800
Is there any popular ground swell in favor or against changes in our atomic policy?

21:06.800 --> 21:14.320
Well, I feel and it's very much along the lines the Governor Stevenson has explained that then

21:15.120 --> 21:21.920
the cut in the Soviet ground force indicates that they appreciate the new type of war that we

21:21.920 --> 21:25.680
would have in the future and that probably they're directing more of their attention to it.

21:26.560 --> 21:31.440
And I think that place is a great burden upon us and upon the chiefs of staff and the

21:31.440 --> 21:37.120
national security council and the president to keep up with modern methods of war so that we can

21:38.160 --> 21:44.640
put emphasis on new developments as they come along. The whole nature of war far as the parent

21:44.640 --> 21:51.440
and the change in the last several years. But while it's quite apparent, it's probably true that

21:51.680 --> 21:57.200
the Soviet cut was just for the purpose of transferring their manpower or getting stronger in

21:57.200 --> 22:03.200
planes and atomic energy and cutting down on great mass land armies. I do think we ought to try

22:03.200 --> 22:09.280
to ascertain if they are in good faith, give them an opportunity of showing some acts of good faith

22:09.280 --> 22:16.720
like raising the iron curtain, giving the satellite the Poland and the other, the other satellite

22:16.800 --> 22:22.240
nations an opportunity of having a free vote. I think the lines of communication must always be

22:22.880 --> 22:28.000
kept open so that we can if there's any chance of them being in good faith act ourselves.

22:28.880 --> 22:35.200
But I think we would be very unwise and cruelhearted to create the slasher armed forces

22:35.920 --> 22:40.080
on the just on the basis of what they've done without knowing more about it. And I think we

22:40.080 --> 22:44.560
ought to tell the people of the world just what our position is. Is there any kind of a step we

22:44.640 --> 22:49.920
should take? For instance, there's a discussion now about cracking down on countries that

22:49.920 --> 22:54.640
start trading too much and strategic goods behind the iron curtain with red China. Should we

22:54.640 --> 23:00.400
modify our stand there? How do you gentlemen feel about that? Well, I frankly feel that I was in

23:00.400 --> 23:06.480
Russia this past year and in the satellite nations too. There's still a whole lot of good will

23:06.480 --> 23:11.040
between the average Russian peasant and the American citizen. They're tremendously interested in

23:11.040 --> 23:16.720
what's going on here. I think if freedom comes to the Soviet Union, it will be through the

23:16.720 --> 23:22.800
evolutionary process and probably not through a revolution. I think we would gain a whole lot

23:23.920 --> 23:32.160
of goodwill and we would pressure for liberty would be stronger. If in non-strategic matters,

23:32.160 --> 23:38.560
particularly if we could send missions with them, if we did allow some non-strategic trading,

23:39.440 --> 23:43.600
I think we ought to try to get all the information, all the American influence, the influence of

23:43.600 --> 23:48.480
the west behind the iron curtain that we possibly can. Now, Governor Stevenson, you have been

23:48.480 --> 23:53.200
particularly interested in these uncommitted nations as you call them. What do you think perhaps

23:53.200 --> 23:59.840
our changes should be toward them? The scientist speaks of Russia. How about India, Indonesia?

23:59.840 --> 24:04.720
I think our policy has been as you suggested the moment ago, the word you suggested was negative.

24:04.720 --> 24:10.240
I think our policy for the last three years, instead of being forward-looking, instead of taking

24:10.240 --> 24:16.400
instead of identifying ourselves with the revolution of the rising expectations of these newly

24:16.400 --> 24:23.040
independent nations, our attitude has been one of rigidity, one of mistrust, one of suspicion,

24:23.040 --> 24:30.640
one of always quating everything to what we can get out of it in the sense of military commitments,

24:31.360 --> 24:40.560
and the sense of rejection of the concept of neutralism. This has had, of course, disastrous effects

24:40.560 --> 24:46.320
in the loss of prestige and influence by the United States. We've rested our security largely on

24:46.320 --> 24:55.360
military packs and on military aid. The over emphasis on the military, the rigidity of our attitudes

24:55.360 --> 25:01.520
for the most part, and so much of the dialogue that's conducted in this country has had an

25:01.520 --> 25:05.840
unfortunate effect. Now, I think we should change that, and I'm happy to say that within the very

25:05.840 --> 25:11.280
last few weeks there's been some evidence of a change. The Secretary of State, Mr. Dulles,

25:11.600 --> 25:16.480
has begun to talk a little more sympathetically and understandably about neutralism. After all,

25:16.480 --> 25:21.760
this United States was neutral for 150 years. We ought to know more about it and be more understanding

25:21.760 --> 25:27.280
about it than anyone else. In addition to that, even now we're going to talk a little about

25:27.280 --> 25:34.240
more flexibility with respect to aid. Under emphasizing, I hope, the military. I think these are

25:35.120 --> 25:42.000
in the right direction. I have myself, as you perhaps know, Mr. Howe proposed that we could do a lot

25:42.000 --> 25:48.400
to neutralize the new Soviet challenge in the economic field, which has come upon us if we were to

25:49.040 --> 25:54.000
distribute aid, at least in part, through the United Nations rather than bilaterally.

25:54.640 --> 26:00.480
That until we make use of these methods, which will force the Russians in turn to be responsible,

26:00.480 --> 26:08.160
and to deal multilaterally, we will be always in this auction system of bargaining, and always

26:08.160 --> 26:16.480
under the possibility of blackmail, of the threat, that if you don't do what we want for you,

26:16.480 --> 26:21.120
we'll go communist. I'm going to exercise my authority here as the traffic cop and get us out of

26:21.120 --> 26:25.120
this parking lot, where in many ways, press we should have stayed for the whole time, because

26:25.120 --> 26:30.240
there's certainly no more important issue. I would like to express my views very briefly,

26:30.960 --> 26:38.320
and perhaps specifically on the subject we've been talking about. I agree that we placed too

26:38.320 --> 26:44.000
much reliance on military power. I think more specifically, we've made a mistake in letting

26:44.000 --> 26:49.040
NATO fall apart. We haven't tried to unify it. I do not think we've properly supported the

26:49.040 --> 26:54.240
United Nations until right recently. I do not think we've made clear our obligation in the

26:54.240 --> 27:00.560
Middle East that we will stand by a friend, Israel, even though she may be in a tough situation,

27:00.560 --> 27:06.720
and also try to solve the question of the refugees. I think we've played out, we talked out

27:06.720 --> 27:11.200
of both sides of our mouths on the issue of colonialism, and have lost many of our friends in

27:11.200 --> 27:18.240
Southeastern Asia. I think we have been letting the Soviet leaders act, and we have been reacting,

27:18.240 --> 27:24.640
and I think that we're going to have to again return to our heritage as a nation, that we want to

27:24.640 --> 27:30.080
help nations have the people have the right of self-determination and self-government when they're

27:30.080 --> 27:36.080
capable of having it. Then we will have regained the respect and the admiration and the friendship

27:36.080 --> 27:40.960
of the world when we do that. Well, I'd like to get us now onto this issue that time. Sure,

27:40.960 --> 27:44.720
Looms lodge here in Florida, and a lot of other parts of the country too, and you both know what

27:44.720 --> 27:51.520
that is, segregation. Suppose we start with Governor Stevenson from Illinois, and he has done very

27:51.520 --> 27:57.280
well in the Illinois primary, although he was considered to be a little moderate on some aspects

27:57.280 --> 28:03.360
of the segregation issue, and yet in the Chicago, you've got a very big popular vote. How do you feel,

28:03.360 --> 28:09.760
Governor, about your stand on segregation? Do you feel that you have a stand that is going to

28:09.760 --> 28:16.080
track wild support among colored voters and northern city dwellers in not necessarily being in too

28:16.080 --> 28:23.520
much of a hurry? Well, sir, I think so. I don't know that my stand is novel in any way, shape or form.

28:23.520 --> 28:32.880
I have expressed it on many occasions. I've said that the Supreme Court has expressed, I believe,

28:32.880 --> 28:38.560
the conscience of the nation. It certainly has expressed my in this decision on desegregation.

28:38.560 --> 28:43.600
It is also expressed what I think was inevitable. The progress that we have made towards full

28:44.080 --> 28:49.840
the realization of full and equal rights for our minority groups has been tremendous in the past 20

28:49.840 --> 28:57.120
years. This is another major step forward. The court has told us what must be done, and now the

28:57.120 --> 29:02.800
lower courts are assigned the task of telling us when it must be done. I think the problem remains

29:02.960 --> 29:09.440
as to how it is to be done. It's gratifying to me that one half, I believe, roughly one half of all of the

29:10.240 --> 29:15.360
formerly segregated school districts in the country in two years, and it's only been two years,

29:15.360 --> 29:22.080
are now desegregated. But little by little will come down to the hardcore. The difficult stubborn,

29:22.080 --> 29:26.800
sticky places. These will be the deep southern states. These are major social adjustments.

29:27.440 --> 29:31.600
I've said that these major social adjustments, like all social adjustments, require

29:32.400 --> 29:38.240
are difficult and they require time. They also must be accompanied in this

29:38.240 --> 29:44.320
agent day with the greatest understanding and the greatest cooperation I would hope.

29:44.320 --> 29:49.280
And I had hoped also that the president might have intervened in this matter and seen fit to call

29:49.360 --> 29:56.400
in. The leaders of both races in Washington to see what could be done to ease this over.

29:56.400 --> 30:01.920
This transition is this very major and important adjustment. We have to go ahead with it. It has

30:01.920 --> 30:06.560
to be done. That's the law. But now, Senator Kiefer, I don't imagine you'd perhaps disagree

30:06.560 --> 30:11.280
very much with any of the opinions of Governor Stevenson, but you're from a border state. You did not

30:11.280 --> 30:15.520
sign this southern manifesto, a court decision, a Supreme Court decision that some senators would

30:15.760 --> 30:20.640
clear the south sign. How do you find that this stand that you're taking, which is not too far from

30:20.640 --> 30:25.200
the Governor's defense? And how is that affecting your prospects in the southern part of the country?

30:26.000 --> 30:31.680
Well, sir, the Supreme Court decision came right in the middle of the time I was running for

30:31.680 --> 30:39.520
re-election in 1954 in Tennessee. And I said at that time, as I've said since, that the Supreme

30:39.520 --> 30:44.960
Court decision is the law of the land. And any man who takes the oath as president of the United

30:44.960 --> 30:51.200
States, I said since, must take an oath that he is going to uphold the Supreme Court, the law of

30:51.200 --> 30:57.360
the land and the Constitution. And certainly, I wouldn't think false oath in that respect.

30:58.160 --> 31:02.240
I want to say in the first place that it's not only in the south that we have the scrimminations.

31:03.200 --> 31:09.360
We have the scrimminations of Mexican Americans, Oriental Americans, and many parts of the country,

31:09.360 --> 31:14.720
Spanish Americans, and many part in their discriminations between the races and the north.

31:15.600 --> 31:21.200
So that this matter of an equal, fair, full chance for everybody is a nationwide problem.

31:21.840 --> 31:26.240
But of course, we do have a particular problem in the connection with the integration of the schools.

31:27.200 --> 31:32.480
The Supreme Court has spoken, and that is the law of the land. The Supreme Court, of course,

31:32.480 --> 31:37.840
I recognize that there are, there's going to take patience, that there are different situations

31:37.840 --> 31:43.600
in different communities that will require some special treatment and consideration.

31:44.560 --> 31:51.760
But I want to say as a southerner, and as one who has four bears have lived in the south for a long,

31:51.760 --> 31:57.440
long time, that I know the south is going to stay in the mainstream of this great American life.

31:58.400 --> 32:03.760
We have contributed much. The Supreme Court decision places the primary responsibility

32:03.760 --> 32:09.200
upon the school boards in the south with the federal district courts acting as the referees.

32:10.160 --> 32:16.960
And I know that our people have the intelligence. They have the enough spirit of brotherly love

32:16.960 --> 32:23.360
and wanting to do the right thing. We can work out this problem rightly and justly

32:24.000 --> 32:32.960
without sacrificing our public school system and without violence, without causing difficulties.

32:32.960 --> 32:37.520
I know, and I think, Governor Stevenson and I have both expressed the fact that you,

32:38.080 --> 32:44.160
this is something where you can't use a military coercion. We've got to appeal to the

32:44.160 --> 32:50.000
hearts and minds and to the fairness of people. And I have a very firm conviction that our own people

32:50.000 --> 32:56.080
have the fairness and the ability and the intelligence to handle this problem ourselves.

32:56.640 --> 33:02.320
I do feel as Governor Collins here in Florida has suggested that the president calling a

33:02.320 --> 33:08.480
conference of governors, calling in the school boards. Maybe people representing both races to

33:10.400 --> 33:17.840
first keep it in perspective and to keep it out of the hands of violent people. I could do much to

33:17.840 --> 33:23.600
help solve this matter. But it can be, and I don't think it's going to cause a disruption of our

33:23.600 --> 33:30.080
democratic party because the winds of freedom and the demand to be equal and to have a

33:31.040 --> 33:36.400
right to have, of course, all around the world today. Speaking of the disruption of the democratic

33:36.400 --> 33:42.560
party, that brings up the Texas situation there where Senator Johnson did so well and the new

33:42.560 --> 33:46.400
setup of the primary for the convention. How do you feel about that, Governor Stevenson? Would you

33:46.400 --> 33:52.720
like to comment on that? Well, I was delighted. I think if it was a question of Governor

33:52.720 --> 33:58.640
Schivers or Speaker Sam Rayburn and Lyndon Johnson, I think there couldn't be any question as to

33:58.720 --> 34:02.560
what's best for the democratic party, what's best for Texas, and what's best for the United States.

34:02.560 --> 34:07.680
And that's Sam Rayburn and Lyndon Johnson. I'd like to say too in that connection that I think

34:07.680 --> 34:15.360
the election in Texas where the unhappy race issue again was used. And the election here in

34:15.360 --> 34:21.680
Florida, both of these have been healthy and reassuring straws in the wind. And that anyone who uses

34:21.680 --> 34:28.400
this issue, this all-important issue, should merely deserve political ends, is going to do us

34:28.400 --> 34:34.560
the Union of Grave to service in this election year. I think that in addition to what the

34:34.560 --> 34:41.120
Senator has said that the proper resolution without disorder and violence of this all-important,

34:41.120 --> 34:47.680
perhaps most important, domestic issue of many years is imperative. It's also the fact that we

34:47.680 --> 34:52.800
must demonstrate to the world that we mean what we say, that we practice what we profess,

34:53.360 --> 34:58.160
and that we in this flexible government, that we have in this country, in contrast to the

34:59.920 --> 35:07.360
autocracies, to the tyrannies, that we can settle a question of this kind without silencing the

35:07.360 --> 35:10.960
opposition. Well, I've asked you, gentlemen, quite a number of questions. Out the perhaps some

35:10.960 --> 35:16.320
questions you would like to ask each other, either on subjects that have come up for this evening,

35:16.320 --> 35:21.040
or comments you might care to make on statements that one or other of you may have made earlier in

35:21.040 --> 35:26.560
the campaign, would you like to ask Governor Stevenson a question, Senator Kekeover, and then

35:26.560 --> 35:31.840
to turn the compliment, I don't want to do all the question asking. Well, let me say before I

35:31.840 --> 35:38.240
ask any question, I certainly want to join in paying tribute to Senator Johnson and Speaker

35:38.240 --> 35:45.600
Rayburn, and I'm glad that there isn't any question about where Texas is going to be in connection

35:45.680 --> 35:52.720
with the Democratic Party. Well, I've tried not to make any attacks on Governor Stevenson or his

35:53.600 --> 35:59.040
record, and I've regretted that he has made some on me. I think one

36:01.840 --> 36:05.280
matter that he did discuss a good deal after Minnesota, and that's a wonderful state,

36:05.280 --> 36:09.520
and I'd lay that in the middle of it too. I like it too. I wish there weren't so many Republicans.

36:10.240 --> 36:17.200
Well, you carried the most Republican district in Minnesota, so not by now.

36:18.880 --> 36:22.640
But anyway, it's a good state, and we all had a good time. I had a good time in Oregon too,

36:22.640 --> 36:30.160
and I know you had a better time, so that's that. But I was a little bit shocked, I must say,

36:30.160 --> 36:35.280
to find out that right afterwards that you started having a whole lot to say about the fact

36:35.440 --> 36:41.440
that I've been absent on some votes in the United States Senate. Your figures didn't agree with me,

36:41.440 --> 36:48.400
but you made three charges. You said that I'd been absent from votes in 1948 in the Senate,

36:49.440 --> 36:53.920
and the trouble was I wasn't even in the Senate in 1948. That were later to one.

36:55.120 --> 37:02.560
And the second was that I think Governor, that you should have known that the other period that

37:02.560 --> 37:06.960
you picked out that I was in many parts of this nation having hearings,

37:08.000 --> 37:13.600
trying to expose to the sunlight of public opinion, organized crime, criminal elements.

37:14.800 --> 37:19.760
Many people thought we were doing a worthwhile public service. I was excused from the Senate.

37:20.720 --> 37:26.880
I flew back during this time of a year and a half of the Senate Crime Committee for important votes,

37:26.880 --> 37:31.920
just like I flew back from Oregon the other day in Minnesota and California for votes.

37:33.120 --> 37:39.280
And then the third year you picked out was when I was having a life and death race for my own

37:40.960 --> 37:46.560
re-election in 1954 in the state of Tennessee. So I was a little bit surprised at you.

37:50.560 --> 37:56.880
I thought it necessary or proper to at least talk about this voting absenteeism as you call it,

37:56.880 --> 37:58.880
without at least pointing out these reasons.

37:58.880 --> 38:05.040
But I've got Mr. Davis that you got some questions or observations maybe that you would like to make.

38:05.040 --> 38:11.920
I think that if I were a candidate, I'm sorry. I was asked to explain why it was that there were so

38:12.720 --> 38:18.800
that the Senate had little support in the Senate. And I said that I thought possibly among his fellow

38:18.800 --> 38:24.640
senators that possibly one reason for it was that many of them felt that he had not done as much

38:24.640 --> 38:32.320
of the committee work as he should have and that I referred to the 83rd Congress. But I'd be

38:32.320 --> 38:39.920
quite willing to drop the matter to Senate once. Senator Kirsto in the 83rd Congress, I believe the

38:40.720 --> 38:48.480
question of absenteeism was covered by the congressional quarterly. And those figures of course were

38:48.480 --> 38:55.520
not flattering to the senator. It may have been that during that period he was had to be in Tennessee

38:55.520 --> 39:00.000
and the interest of his re-election. If so, I'm quite content with that explanation. I should

39:00.000 --> 39:04.720
like him to understand that the occasion for my mentioning this was in response to questions.

39:06.320 --> 39:11.360
Well, it seemed to have been the main part of an address that you made for us I could see.

39:13.200 --> 39:18.400
I said something more important than that. I'm certain Adelaide that you were not around

39:19.280 --> 39:22.880
the governor's chair in Springfield very much during the fall that you were running for

39:24.080 --> 39:28.720
as a democratic nominee for the president. So when you were in a race that's very difficult to

39:28.720 --> 39:32.560
be there very often. But the Senate was in the session when the race was on. Was it?

39:33.440 --> 39:38.480
Oh yes, when our primaries on, our primaries are held in the early part of August so that you have to

39:38.480 --> 39:45.120
run during May June and July. At any way you say that you were answering questions about the lack

39:45.120 --> 39:51.680
of support in the Senate. I haven't put any effort on my pressure on my colleagues to try to

39:51.680 --> 39:59.120
get support. I do have the support of some of my senators, some of my congressmen. I think I'll

39:59.120 --> 40:05.280
have more before it's over. The trouble was you started earlier and they've got many of them to

40:05.280 --> 40:11.440
sign up and agree with you. But I was glad to see in the congressional quarterly that I was tied

40:11.520 --> 40:17.280
for second place with congressional support along with Senator Lyndon Johnson for second place.

40:18.160 --> 40:23.920
And that's pretty good company to be in. I wonder if we could get on to another question. Now both

40:23.920 --> 40:28.720
of you gentlemen have traveled a great deal and shaken a lot of hands and talked to all kinds of

40:28.720 --> 40:34.240
people. I'd be interesting to find out what your sounding show of the people that you've talked to.

40:34.240 --> 40:39.360
What interests them? What do these people that you shake hands with and you get letters from and

40:39.360 --> 40:44.320
all at your mail? How does that run? What are the American people? Tumbled about, hopeful about,

40:44.320 --> 40:51.280
what do you gentlemen hear from the real grassroots? Senator, before you ask me,

40:51.280 --> 40:57.600
yes I think it's your turn. The main thing in the agricultural sections, and this is true all

40:57.600 --> 41:06.960
over the United States. The farmer's income has gone down about 27%. Their expenses are not going

41:06.960 --> 41:12.640
down. They've even risen. They have a fixed overhead that they must meet. So farmers,

41:12.640 --> 41:17.840
particularly small farmers, have been having a very hard time of it. They are in favor of an

41:17.840 --> 41:24.240
agricultural program that's going to give them a fair share of the nation's income. And in order to

41:24.240 --> 41:29.440
get prices that will bear a reasonable relationship to what they have to pay for what they get.

41:30.400 --> 41:36.160
That's what I've been trying to fight for. And I find particularly among the small farmers that there's

41:36.160 --> 41:41.760
a, that we have lost a million small farmers. Small farmers are not able to stay on the land.

41:42.960 --> 41:46.800
So that I found a good deal of interest and a proposal that I've been making for a

41:47.920 --> 41:54.720
so-called family size farm bill to have full or 100% parity for the first

41:55.760 --> 41:59.360
small part of a farmer's income and then have it graduated on down.

42:00.560 --> 42:05.280
So that the small farmer can at least get some protection that he can know about.

42:06.240 --> 42:12.240
And this is met with a great deal of a good reception. And I think if we're going to protect

42:12.240 --> 42:17.840
the small farmer and keep that this very valuable influence in our social and economic and

42:17.840 --> 42:22.480
political life that some special measures like this are going to have to be taken.

42:22.480 --> 42:26.880
Governor Stevenson, I think you were due for a little time now.

42:27.280 --> 42:32.400
Well, sir, I would say that the senator is quite right. And in many sections of the country,

42:33.280 --> 42:40.000
especially the rural agricultural sections of the country, the farm issue. And they're very

42:40.000 --> 42:47.200
rapid decline in farm income. The 27% drop in three years is the domestic issue of principal

42:47.200 --> 42:54.320
concern. It is also an, it's also a concern in becoming a concern in certain industrial areas

42:54.320 --> 43:00.960
because of the, of the effect that it's inevitably would have because of our economic

43:00.960 --> 43:06.560
interdependence on employment in certain aspects of industry, particularly in farm implement

43:06.560 --> 43:12.400
manufacture, where I believe farm interdependence is now down more than 20% in the first quarter of

43:12.400 --> 43:19.200
this year. And the result is large layoffs in Chicago and in Minneapolis and various other farm

43:19.200 --> 43:25.360
implement centers. It's also having effect on small business in the small towns, the merchant,

43:25.360 --> 43:31.360
the farmer can't buy shoes. If he, I mean, if he can't sell, if he's caught in this cost price

43:31.360 --> 43:37.040
squeeze as he is, he can't, his purchasing power is diminished. And obviously the effect of that

43:37.040 --> 43:44.160
is that he's unable to buy hardware, furniture, clothing and so on in the local market. And the

43:44.160 --> 43:48.160
small business man is suffering. Did I give you, Governor Stevenson, a chance to ask your question

43:48.160 --> 43:52.960
senator, keep all the, perhaps I, we spent all our time in his question to you when you are

43:52.960 --> 43:55.760
a flyaway. Did you have any other question you want to ask him? I'm not sure. I'm not sure. I'd

43:55.760 --> 44:01.520
ask him when he was going back to California. I don't know what to get about. I guess we'll be out about

44:01.520 --> 44:07.760
the same day. Well, Governor Stevenson started mentioning something that's very important.

44:08.800 --> 44:13.840
The effect on small business, small business and middle size of business and merchants were having

44:13.840 --> 44:18.080
a rough time of it. Their profits are there, I'm considerably, while there's big business

44:18.080 --> 44:25.200
is up. I think we need several things and we all have a strong program to try to keep small

44:25.200 --> 44:31.600
business in the picture. When I think that we must revise our antitrust laws, strengthen our

44:31.600 --> 44:40.240
Robinson Patman Act S11, which Congressman Patman and I have filed, we should have a notification

44:40.240 --> 44:45.120
period when a merger is going to take place or is to try to stop this merger effort. Small

44:45.120 --> 44:50.480
business ought to be able to have a better situation in the tax picture to have the surtax

44:50.480 --> 44:56.320
started 50,000. Then we need desperately some agency in Washington that will enable small business

44:56.320 --> 45:04.000
to get some of the procurement from the defense department and others and also to furnish them

45:04.000 --> 45:09.520
equity capital when necessary. But unless something's done for our small businesses and unless this

45:09.520 --> 45:16.560
great merger movement, which is giving small business people stronger and stronger and worse

45:16.560 --> 45:21.840
competition, we are going to have more and more of this country in the hands of fewer and fewer

45:21.840 --> 45:26.800
people, which is not a good situation. The situation is serious and I think perhaps more serious

45:26.800 --> 45:32.320
as to how many of our listeners tonight, viewers tonight, will realize especially in the

45:33.280 --> 45:40.080
East. I believe that bankruptcies now in small business, small business failures are at a higher

45:40.080 --> 45:47.920
rate than they have been at any time since 1941. Profits were off last year over the previous two years

45:47.920 --> 45:54.640
by something like 66%. This is a critical matter. The senator has mentioned, I think one of the

45:54.640 --> 46:02.160
major problems, of course, is credit. Availability of credit for them to operate, but it's a trend that

46:02.160 --> 46:08.560
is going on and it's a serious thing and it presents very fundamental philosophical considerations

46:08.560 --> 46:13.760
that trend towards bigness. I'd like to ask another more general question perhaps and that is both

46:13.760 --> 46:19.280
of you have campaigned very hard in the primaries. You've used all kinds of techniques. Back in 48,

46:19.280 --> 46:24.160
the Harry Truman did pretty well with the old-fashioned whistle stop in 52, present Eisenhower did well

46:24.160 --> 46:29.440
with modern TV. How do you appraise these various means of reaching the public today?

46:29.840 --> 46:34.720
Well, this is very important, this television, if you have money to buy it, we haven't had much

46:34.720 --> 46:41.600
money to have in it. Radio, of course, newspapers, but I think there's nothing like getting out and

46:42.400 --> 46:46.400
talking with and finding out what the people are thinking, meeting the people personally.

46:47.440 --> 46:53.200
My friend and Governor Stevens has taken that up. I saw where he was shaking hands with a wax

46:53.760 --> 46:58.240
model down in the store the other day. Tempted. Found a very tempting.

47:00.720 --> 47:07.360
Well, I just say that you've been doing better recently than I have.

47:08.640 --> 47:14.720
I think in addition, Mr. Howe to the what Sunder said, the problem of the use of these

47:14.720 --> 47:21.520
media is a very cute one. It's going to get a major test in the forthcoming campaign. Obviously,

47:21.520 --> 47:29.360
the cost of television on any large scale is very, very high. Yet that is the medium that reaches

47:29.360 --> 47:35.040
the most people. And the hour is always an hour, and even though it seems like no time at all,

47:35.040 --> 47:38.560
the time has now come, the hour has not, but the time for the discussion has run out and the

47:38.560 --> 47:43.120
summation has come. Each of you has five minutes, as you know, to sum up under a general heading

47:43.120 --> 47:48.560
of why I am a candidate, and as I explained earlier, Toss of the coin gave Governor Stevenson

47:48.560 --> 47:53.600
the chance to put his statement first, Senator Keith, all the second, and now we will hear first

47:53.600 --> 47:58.800
from the Governor Stevenson in the first of the summations in five minutes why I am a candidate.

48:01.840 --> 48:10.160
I don't think that anyone, Mr. Howe, runs for President or should run for the presidency of the

48:10.160 --> 48:16.800
United States in this age and day, just to serve a personal ambition, or just because you want

48:16.800 --> 48:21.920
the job or would like the work. I think you run for President because you have profound

48:22.720 --> 48:29.040
convictions about the principles of your party, that you have profound convictions about the

48:29.040 --> 48:35.600
state of the Union and the world in which we live, and that you have some idea at least about what

48:35.600 --> 48:42.080
should be done about it. When you have those in combination, and you also are beset by many

48:43.040 --> 48:49.120
many leaders of your party, as well as the rank and file, to undertake this most responsible,

48:50.640 --> 49:00.000
this most responsible task in democratic society, I think you do it and you don't spare yourself.

49:01.520 --> 49:08.320
You don't spare yourself from the body. I, your body from the back. I felt that I had all of those

49:09.120 --> 49:15.040
circumstances in combination, and in addition to that, I had strong convictions about some of the

49:15.040 --> 49:20.800
things that I think are wrong with our country. I have a feeling that the President of the

49:20.800 --> 49:25.840
Government, the Eisenhower administration, is basically a single interest government, that it is

49:26.480 --> 49:32.400
manned and staffed at the top of the policy-making positions, and proponderably by people

49:32.400 --> 49:37.520
representative of only one interest in our community, call it big business, call it big money,

49:37.520 --> 49:42.480
call it big industry, or call it what you please. And the government to be successful must be

49:43.040 --> 49:48.560
representative and reflect the interests of all of our people, and that this government does not.

49:49.200 --> 49:55.120
I felt that, and that my party, traditionally, has been the party of all the people, and that it

49:55.120 --> 50:00.560
was the best instrument to bring that about. In addition, I felt very strongly about a variety of

50:00.560 --> 50:05.120
issues of which we have mentioned here, of which I should like to mention more, the conservation

50:05.200 --> 50:12.800
of our resources, the development of our resources, about the Bill of Rights, about our liberties,

50:12.800 --> 50:19.520
if you please, and the abuses that they have suffered in late years. And countless other domestic

50:19.520 --> 50:25.120
issues, which I'm afraid time does not permit me to mention, but transcendent and more important

50:25.120 --> 50:30.560
even than all of those, is the problem of war and peace in the world. We have this great domestic

50:31.520 --> 50:36.400
issue of the relationship, the tensions that are rising, unhappily between the races in this

50:36.400 --> 50:42.560
country which we must master, we just must master. We have an addition to that, this crisis in the

50:42.560 --> 50:47.760
world, this new threat, this new challenge from the Soviet Union. I don't think that we're

50:47.760 --> 50:53.840
faring well in the Cold War, and I think that the reasons are relatively obvious, and that until

50:53.840 --> 51:00.080
we can, once more, until the image of America is clear and distinct and decisive, until the

51:00.560 --> 51:06.160
uncommitted peoples, until the underprivileged, underdeveloped, unhappy peoples of the world,

51:06.160 --> 51:12.800
real, who realize that hunger, disease, and the want and oppression are not the immutable destiny

51:12.800 --> 51:17.200
of man, and that we understand that, and we're sympathetic, and that we, the United States,

51:17.920 --> 51:23.760
of creature, of revolution, child of revolution, is their friend, that we will have trouble,

51:24.400 --> 51:31.280
and that we also have to, to not only recapture their confidence, but in addition to that,

51:31.280 --> 51:38.720
we must also make it transparently clear that we are going to continue strong, that we are going

51:38.720 --> 51:46.640
to continue resolute, and that we likewise will never be one to refuse to negotiate, to refuse to talk,

51:46.640 --> 51:54.160
to refuse to meet our enemy's halfway, be it in Egypt now, be it a meeting now, of our foreign

51:54.160 --> 52:01.840
ministers to see what can be done, to resolve the threats that hover over that eastern Mediterranean

52:01.840 --> 52:10.880
in Israel. I have spoken hurriedly, and not too carefully, Mr. Howe, but I can summarize my feeling

52:11.840 --> 52:19.920
that the undertaking to run for president at this time is a, as some, an undertaking is a human being

52:20.960 --> 52:28.320
can attempt. I have done it thoughtfully, I have done it perhaps advisedly because I have done it before,

52:29.680 --> 52:35.600
and I did it under circumstances which gave me satisfaction. I conducted a campaign that I think

52:36.560 --> 52:41.360
myself and my party. I would hope that I might be able to do it again for reasons that I have

52:41.360 --> 52:47.200
indicated and that I feel very deeply. Thank you very much, Governor Stevenson, and now you have

52:47.200 --> 52:51.920
the same opportunity, Senator Keefe, over to address yourself to the same subject and tell us why

52:51.920 --> 52:58.960
you were a candidate. Well, Mr. Howe, the first became interested in 1952, because I've been in the

52:58.960 --> 53:03.440
House of Representatives and the United States Senate for some time, and there were a lot of things

53:03.440 --> 53:09.200
that I wanted to try to do that I thought were important. One of the particular things that

53:09.200 --> 53:16.160
that that time was that it found that organized crime and the criminal element had infiltrated into

53:16.160 --> 53:23.040
politics and to our life and economic life, badly affecting our country, and I wanted our government

53:23.040 --> 53:29.280
to take as strong a position as possible to rid the nation of this element and to keep them under

53:29.280 --> 53:35.120
control. Much has been done, but I think a whole lot more needs to be done and a whole lot is the

53:35.120 --> 53:41.360
federal responsibility. And then in the American tradition and for the sake of a secure and

53:41.360 --> 53:47.360
wholesome economy, I think we must reestablish a fair balance between industry and business,

53:47.360 --> 53:54.080
agriculture and labor, with each receiving his fair share of the national income. Farmers undoubtedly

53:54.080 --> 53:59.360
have been penalized in the last three years. I want them to get a fair price for their products,

53:59.360 --> 54:04.160
and I'm especially interested in working for the welfare of the little farmer, so we won't lose

54:04.160 --> 54:09.840
this very valuable part of our American life. Now, I think we must see to it that labor and labor

54:09.840 --> 54:17.200
unions can work and organize under a fair labor relations law, and the interest of that will be

54:17.200 --> 54:23.040
fair to labor and to management and to the public too. I don't think the taft hardly law is such a law.

54:23.600 --> 54:30.320
It denies a union protection to a great many people. I think it ought to be drastically revised and

54:30.320 --> 54:35.760
rewritten in many respects. And then I've always been interested in the welfare of small business

54:35.760 --> 54:40.880
for a long time. I think we must protect in many ways that I talked about a little while ago with

54:40.880 --> 54:47.120
a small and the middle-sized businessman and the merchant against the avalanche of economic

54:47.120 --> 54:53.040
concentration, which is coming up in this nation today. I'm very much interested in social security

54:53.040 --> 54:57.280
and old age assistance legislation. I've worked for them ever since I've been in public life.

54:58.080 --> 55:02.400
I want us to amend our social security law at this session of Congress, if possible, who

55:03.040 --> 55:08.480
tell you those who are totally and permanently disabled at 50 years of age. And we must see that our

55:08.480 --> 55:16.080
old age assistance laws are extended and that the determents are taken out of the way so that our

55:16.960 --> 55:24.080
elderly citizens can live with dignity and without want in their last years. I'm interested very much

55:24.080 --> 55:30.080
in education. I want us to as long as we have a single child who doesn't have an educational

55:30.080 --> 55:36.320
opportunity. As long as our teachers are underpaid, I feel that we do have a very important challenge

55:36.320 --> 55:41.280
in which the federal government must play a part. I have of course been interested in resource

55:41.280 --> 55:47.120
development and I want our federal government to play its part in trying to see that great projects

55:47.120 --> 55:53.840
like the Southern and Central Valley floor of project are carried on that rivers of our, the water

55:53.840 --> 55:59.360
of our rivers are harnessed for the benefit of our people for irrigation and for power. We must

55:59.360 --> 56:07.040
keep this in nation of increasing opportunities for all of our people. And I feel also that in the

56:07.120 --> 56:15.520
world today that if we would just use our spiritual and economic influence, our great strength as a

56:15.520 --> 56:21.120
nation with all of our ties to many other nations and interests of peace, that we can have peace with

56:21.120 --> 56:27.040
honor in our lifetime. And that's very important to the young people of this nation, to all of us.

56:27.680 --> 56:32.080
I feel in the first place we must take effective steps to hold together the people who believe in

56:32.080 --> 56:40.080
freedom, who believe in democracy and NATO in united nations. Also we must take a firm position

56:40.080 --> 56:46.320
against colonialism and be a helper to people who are trying to get self-government because they're

56:46.320 --> 56:53.120
doing just exactly what we did 175 years ago. We must make our position crystal clear in all parts

56:53.120 --> 56:58.560
of the world, like in the Middle East. I think we must formalize and have a non-aggression

56:58.560 --> 57:03.920
tax with offer them to little Israel into the Arab nations and help solve the refugee problem.

57:04.880 --> 57:10.000
We must meet this new Russian smile. We must have a flexible foreign policy so that we can

57:10.880 --> 57:16.960
use our best ambassadors, our best means, our best tradition for the purpose of trying to bring about

57:16.960 --> 57:23.360
peace. In the final analysis, it seems to me that our national security rests not only on our armed

57:23.360 --> 57:29.840
forces, but equally and perhaps even to a more important extent. It resides in our great

57:29.840 --> 57:36.560
conception of government, our belief in democracy and in human freedom. It resides in our

57:36.560 --> 57:42.240
bill of rights and in the Constitution. These are weapons just like other weapons, and if we use

57:42.240 --> 57:48.400
them we can move and stir the hearts of people everywhere. These are all things that we want,

57:49.040 --> 57:53.840
like Sir Thomas Moore said for those things for which we pray, let us have the grace and

57:53.840 --> 57:58.640
strength to the labor. I want to labor for these things and I would like to leave the American people

57:58.640 --> 58:04.160
in trying to get them. That's the reason I want to be president. Thank you. Thank you both.

58:04.160 --> 58:08.800
Very much, Senator Keefeauver and Governor Stevenson, they're especially gratified that the

58:08.800 --> 58:14.960
emphasis you both put on world affairs and I hope the listeners and viewers enjoyed it as much as

58:14.960 --> 58:19.120
I did. I think it's the most important feature of the campaign. I'm glad you took the time on it.

58:19.120 --> 58:23.440
You know the people you've been in touch with them and the fact that you have had this first hand

58:23.440 --> 58:27.840
inside into the way the voters feel and still would like to have given them a whole time to

58:27.840 --> 58:32.880
peace and international affairs. That's one of the most hotening signs of this evening's discussion.

58:33.360 --> 58:39.360
So this is Quincy Howe with Senator Keefeauver and Governor Stevenson saying good night from

58:39.360 --> 58:46.160
studios of WTWTBJ in Miami.

